-- models/intermediate/int_deduped_billing_events.sql
-- Deduplicate billing events to one per subscription + event_month (pick latest event_id)
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        event_id,
        subscription_id,
        event_month,
        amount,
        event_type,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY subscription_id, event_month
            ORDER BY event_id DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_billing_events') }}
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount,
    event_type
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- models/intermediate/int_subscription_company.sql
-- Join subscriptions to users to companies
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        s.subscription_id,
        s.user_id,
        s.plan_id,
        s.started_at,
        s.ended_at,
        s.status,
        u.name,
        u.email,
        u.company_id,
        COALESCE(c.industry, '(unknown)') AS industry
    FROM {{ ref('stg_subscriptions') }} s
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_users') }} u
        ON u.user_id = s.user_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_companies') }} c
        ON c.company_id = u.company_id
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    user_id,
    plan_id,
    started_at,
    ended_at,
    status,
    name,
    email,
    company_id,
    industry
FROM source
```

-- models/intermediate/int_subscription_plan.sql
-- Join subscriptions with plans, handling missing plan records
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        sc.subscription_id,
        sc.user_id,
        sc.plan_id,
        sc.started_at,
        sc.ended_at,
        sc.status,
        sc.name,
        sc.email,
        sc.company_id,
        sc.industry,
        COALESCE(p.tier, '(unknown)') AS tier,
        COALESCE(p.monthly_price, 0) AS monthly_price
    FROM {{ ref('int_subscription_company') }} sc
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_plans') }} p
        ON p.plan_id = sc.plan_id
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    user_id,
    plan_id,
    started_at,
    ended_at,
    status,
    name,
    email,
    company_id,
    industry,
    tier,
    monthly_price
FROM source
```

-- models/intermediate/int_monthly_subscriptions.sql
-- Calculate active subscriptions per month from billing events
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        b.event_month,
        sp.subscription_id,
        sp.user_id,
        sp.tier,
        sp.industry,
        b.amount
    FROM {{ ref('int_deduped_billing_events') }} b
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_subscription_plan') }} sp
        ON sp.subscription_id = b.subscription_id
)
SELECT
    event_month,
    subscription_id,
    user_id,
    tier,
    industry,
    amount
FROM source
```

```sql
-- models/marts/fct_monthly_subscription_metrics.sql
-- Monthly subscription metrics: active subscriptions, MRR, unique users by tier and industry
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        event_month,
        tier,
        industry,
        subscription_id,
        user_id,
        amount
    FROM {{ ref('int_monthly_subscriptions') }}
)
SELECT
    source.event_month AS month,
    source.tier,
    source.industry,
    COUNT(DISTINCT source.subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
    SUM(source.amount) AS total_mrr,
    COUNT(DISTINCT source.user_id) AS unique_users
FROM source
GROUP BY
    source.event_month,
    source.tier,
    source.industry
ORDER BY
    source.event_month ASC,
    source.tier ASC,
    source.industry ASC
